=== Other ===
* One of the shrine’s {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Gonnegi|1=UNKNOWN}} (assistant priests), who is also a motorcyclist, began providing support services for riders. This led to the shrine becoming known as a “Motorcycle Shrine.”<ref>[https://hamamatsu-lab.jp/goout/2327.html Published: 2021/10/04 “Ōtoshi Shrine, the Motorcycle Shrine of Hamamatsu, the Home of Motorcycles” Hamalabo – Hamamatsu Research Institute]</ref><ref>[https://forride.jp/motorcycle/sizuoka-touring Published: 2020/08/23 Updated: 2020/08/23 “A Local Motorcycle Girl’s Guide! Shizuoka Holiday Touring Spots” PLAY For Ride]</ref>

