'''Tennōgū Ōtoshi Shrine''' (てんのうぐうおおとしじんじゃ) is a Shinto shrine located in Tennō-chō, {{ill|lt=Chūō Ward (Hamamatsu City)|Q117084743|WD=Q117084743|lt=Chūō Ward}}, {{ill|lt=Hamamatsu City|Q185125|WD=Q185125}}, {{ill|lt=Shizuoka Prefecture|Q131320|WD=Q131320}}. One of its component shrines, Ōtoshi Shrine, is listed among the {{ill|lt=List of Shikinaisha in Tōtōmi Province|Q11642130|WD=Q11642130|lt=Engishiki shrines}}.

=== History ===
The date of establishment is unknown.  
Originally, the shrine consisted of three separate shrines—{{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Tennōgū|1=UNKNOWN}}, Tennō Shrine, and {{ill|lt=Ōtoshi Shrine|Q11436758|WD=Q11436758}}—which were later merged. Subsequently, the tutelary deities of four parish towns were also enshrined together, resulting in the present form.  
The collective name Tennōgū Ōtoshi Shrine came into use thereafter.

=== Enshrined deities ===
''' Tennōgū '''
